There's a little discussion behind the counter and then one of the lady staff said:"just remake for her" I went to the collection point,and just nice saw the barrister gave 4 pumps of syrup into the grande cup. He then asked the lady a question which I can't hear, and the lady took the cup and gave it another 2 pump. So In total there's 6 pumps of syrup. While waiting for the drink to be done I explained that I think he missed the syrup in the initial cup. Without thinking he said it's because I didn't stir. At that point of time I was too tired and lazy to argue. I took the drink and left. About few steps away I took a sip, and true enough. Syrup is all I taste. And since I wouldn't want to face them again, I simply threw the whole cup away into the bin nearby. Regretted making my way down. Should have just try to enjoy my first latte. Wasted trip, and they are non apologetic at all. What a Friday.
